<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12022c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12022c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12022c"> 22(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pious clamour <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12022c"><li>FW 110.36 </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n12022c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n12022c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12022c">MS BL 47473-32v</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:326 <a name="ed3" href="../../ff/fdra/eda.htm#ed3">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/ed3.htm#n12022c">Draft: I.5&sect;1.3</a>/4.3</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Dans ce dessein, il a r&eacute;uni ses religieux et ils tiennent conseil dans la Crypte de l&apos;Aquilon. L&apos;Abb&eacute; leur a expos&eacute; les ravages que Jean de Thomas exerce sur les terres de l&apos;abbaye, et, apr&egrave;s une courte d&eacute;lib&eacute;ration, les b&eacute;n&eacute;dictins d&eacute;cident, &mdash; ce qui est imm&eacute;diatement transcrit sur les registres des Actes &mdash; que &ldquo;sans <i>omettre un seul jour, il sera c&eacute;l&eacute;br&eacute;, devant l&apos;autel Saint-Michel, pendant que l&apos;on chantera la messe, une</i> CLAMEUR TR&Egrave;S PIEUSE <i>en pr&eacute;sence du Tr&egrave;s-Saint et tr&egrave;s v&eacute;ritable Corps de Notre-Seigneur J&eacute;sus-Christ, chantant avec larmes</i> MISERERE MEI<i> et clamant</i> KYRIE ELEISON!&rdquo; &hellip; Voil&agrave; une semaine que la clameur tr&egrave;s pieuse s&apos;&eacute;l&egrave;ve vers l&apos;Archange, et la fureur de Jean, loin de s&apos;arr&ecirc;ter, augmente encore! <br>[<i>The clamour of the monks</i>: In this plan he has brought together his monks and they hold council in the Crypt of the Aquilon. The Abbot has told them about the ravages of Jean de Thomas on the lands of the abbey, and, after a short deliberation, the Benedictines decide, which is immediately entered in the register of the Acts, that &lsquo;without omitting a single day, there will be a celebration, before the altar of Saint Michel, while one chants mass, a VERY <mark>PIOUS CLAMOUR</mark> in the presence of the Most Holy and True Body of Our Lord Jesus Christ, chanting with tears MISERERE MEI and clamouring KYRIE ELEISON.&rsquo; For a week the very pious clamour rises to the Archangel and the fury of Jean, instead of abating, is still rising! <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 63-4 [La clameur des moines]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
